I just don't buy the false dilemma +steve taylor. Let's start by looking at the Earth before the advent of man. It managed to survive for billions of years without either stagnating or running out of energy. In a similar way, if we top off at the 10 billion in population that the UN predicts (and I believe we will) and if we learn to use the available energy with increasing efficiency (as we already are), there's no reason to think we will stagnate just because we are not "growing".

But you are right that Heat Death awaits us at some point, so our choices are to beat that somehow or we might as well just give up now? I can think of a multitude of futures that can fill the places between those extremes.﻿
